Pairs with the SDL-side patch (patches/SDL/0021-…) that default-skips
the DOS_Yield in DOSVESA_PumpEvents. With that yield removed, the
cooperative audio thread no longer gets scheduled time on every input
poll — it would starve. Add an explicit SDL_Delay(0) once per flip in
Renderer::flip() after RenderPresent / GetWindowSurface refresh, which
routes through SDL_SYS_DelayNS(0) → DOS_Yield() on the DOS backend.

At 15 fps target this is one yield every ~67 ms — well within one
audio chunk's worth of buffering (186 ms at 22050 Hz stereo S16,
default 4096-frame chunks).

Also extends initVideo's diagnostic block to log whether the SDL-side
pump yield is "skipped (default)" or "FORCED-ON" via env var, so
DEBUG.LOG iter captures record which mode is active.

See docs/PHASE9-NEXT-WAVES-PLAN.md §6 wave 13.2 ablation table for the
115 ms NO_INPUT_POLL measurement that motivated this fix.
---
 src/graphics/Renderer.cpp | 19 +++++++++++++++++++
 1 file changed, 19 insertions(+)

diff --git a/src/graphics/Renderer.cpp b/src/graphics/Renderer.cpp
index 02e171e..fd270a9 100644
--- a/src/graphics/Renderer.cpp
+++ b/src/graphics/Renderer.cpp
@@ -1028,6 +1028,17 @@ bool Renderer::initVideo()
            _abl_no_dc_timing() ? 1 : 0,
            _abl_cache_winsurf() ? 1 : 0,
            _abl_no_input_poll_env() ? 1 : 0);
+  // DOS-PORT (patch 0064, Phase 9 wave 13.3): log whether the SDL-side
+  // PumpEvents yield-skip is active. Default ON (skip); env-var override
+  // SDL_HINT_DOSKUTSU_FORCE_PUMP_YIELD=1 restores the original yield.
+  {
+    const char *force_yield = SDL_getenv("SDL_HINT_DOSKUTSU_FORCE_PUMP_YIELD");
+    const bool yield_forced = force_yield && force_yield[0] == '1' && force_yield[1] == 0;
+    LOG_INFO("Renderer::initVideo: DOSVESA pump yield: {} "
+             "(per-flip explicit SDL_Delay(0) yield is always on; "
+             "set SDL_HINT_DOSKUTSU_FORCE_PUMP_YIELD=1 to restore old per-pump yield)",
+             yield_forced ? "FORCED-ON" : "skipped (default)");
+  }
   // First frame must be a full refresh — we have no last-frame
   // history to compare against and the backbuffer state is whatever
   // SDL3 initialized it to.
@@ -1368,6 +1379,14 @@ void Renderer::flip()
   // — re-query may be running fb_state populate inside SDL3-DOS).
   if (!_abl_cache_winsurf())
     _cached_window_surface = SDL_GetWindowSurface(_window);
+
+  // DOS-PORT (patch 0064, Phase 9 wave 13.3): explicit cooperative-thread
+  // yield once per flip. Pairs with the SDL-side patch that removes the
+  // per-pump DOS_Yield from DOSVESA_PumpEvents. SDL_Delay(0) routes to
+  // SDL_SYS_DelayNS(0) → DOS_Yield() on the DOS backend, giving the
+  // audio thread scheduled time without the 115 ms round-trip cost
+  // measured in wave 13.2 NO_INPUT_POLL ablation.
+  SDL_Delay(0);
   if (!ok)
   {
     ++_flip_failed;
